description:
&lt;p&gt;Salisbury NHS Foundation Trust is looking for an Infrastructure Engineer with demonstrable experience in enterprise IT, infrastructure and networking within a complex large organisation. Work will include analysis, recommending solutions, migrating, archiving and decommissioning systems in line with business needs and adherence to data protection legislation. Knowledge of Microsoft Windows operating systems is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you forward thinking and focused with a &#39;can do&#39; attitude? Do you have the drive and ability to identify problems and present information to senior stakeholders? A proactive stance and attention to detail is a must, combined with previous exposure to document writing, system design and implementation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be closely aligned with projects and a Cyber Security team, so must be a team player. Alongside internal colleagues, they will be required to liaise with third party suppliers and staff from other NHS organisations. The successful candidate must be able to manage and prioritise their own workload under the direction of senior IT managers and programme managers to ensure corporate objectives are met.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wendy Bacon Senior Project Manager, Transformation &amp; Informatics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;wendy.bacon3@nhs.net 01722 336262 ext 5698 &lt;/p&gt;
